        "last_activity_date": 1689368469,
        "creation_date": 1689367801,
        "body": "<p>You need to use <code>@Autowired<\/code> or <code>@Inject<\/code> to get the bean for the <code>A<\/code> component. Spring handles the dependency injection, so if you try to create an instance on your own outside the application context, the <code>ServiceClass<\/code> will not be injected.<\/p>\n<p>If you want to run some code after your class has been properly created, you can annotate a method with <code>@PostConstruct<\/code>.<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>@Component\npublic class B {\n    @Inject;\n    A a;\n    \n    @PostConstruct\n    private void postConstruct() {\n        a.callsomeutility();\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
        "answer_id": 76691045,
